;color:rgb(34,34,34);\">》</span></div>", "<span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\">Review</span>"], "授業外学習2": "As a general rule, students should expect to spend one to two minutes of study outside of class for every minute of class time."}, "評価": {"教科書/Required texts0": ["Marijke Breuning, \"Foreign Policy Analysis: A Comparative Introduction,\" (Palgrave MacMillan, 2007), ISBN: 978-0-3122-9619-3\nDVD: Errol Morris, Dir., \"The Fog of War/フォッグ　オブ　ウォー,\" (Columbia Pictures/Tristar, 2009), ASIN: B002AEG0IU\nJames G. Blight and Janet M. Lang, \"The Fog of War,\" (Rowman and Littlefield, 2005), ISBN: 978-0-7425-4221-1"], "教科書/Required texts1": ["Marijke Breuning", "Foreign Policy Analysis: A Comparative Introduction", "Palgrave Macmillan", "2007 年", "978-0-3122-9619-3", ""], "教科書/Required texts2": ["Errol Morris", "DVD: The Fog of War/フォッグ　オブ　ウォー", "Columbia Pictures/Tristar", "2009 年", "ASIN:  B002AEG0IU", ""], "教科書/Required texts3": ["James G. Blight and Janet M. Lang", "The Fog of War", "Rowman and Littlefield", "2005 年", "978-0-7425-4221-1", ""], "参考書/Reference books0": ["著者名\nAuthor", "タイトル\nTitle", "発行所\nPublisher", "出版年\nYear of Publication", "ISBN", "ボタン\nButton"], "参考書/Reference books1": ["Valerie M. Hudson and Benjamin S. Day", "Foreign Policy Analysis: Classic and Contemporary Theory", "Rowman and Littlefield", "2020 年", "9781442277922", ""], "参考文献・資料/Reference books0": ["Valerie M. Hudson and Benjamin S. Day, \"Foreign Policy Analysis: Classic and Contemporary Theory,\" (Rowman and Littlefield, 2020), ISBN: 9781442277922"], "学位授与の方針との関連Relationship to Diploma Policy0": ["Each course is positioned within the curriculum in accordance with the diploma policy andcurriculum policy established by each undergraduate/graduate school. By proceeding with the study of this course with an awareness of the DP and CP, the following abilities expected by each undergraduate/graduate school will be developed.Global Studies:1. Understanding and analytical skills regarding international issues: the ability to understand and analyze various regions of the world from different perspectives in the humanities and social sciences.2. Problem-solving skills: the ability to proactively identify problems and solve them based on appropriate methods.3. Intercultural understanding and multicultural coexistence: the ability to be sensitive to different cultures and to coexist with diverse cultures."], "成績評価Grading0": ["種別　Type備考　Note", "割合　Percentage", "評価基準等　Grading Criteria etc."], "成績評価Grading1": ["授業中試験／In-class examination (03)", "50 %", ""], "成績評価Grading2": ["授業への参加度（自発性、積極性、主体性、等）／In-class participation,contribution (09)", "50 %", "Participation"], "成績評価Grading3": ["備考　Note Students will be expected to attend and participate in class discussions and may be asked to complete small assignments from time to time. These will all factor into the participation grade which is 50 percent of the final grade. Finally, there will be a final essay in class worth 50 percent of the grade."], "更新日時/Date of Update0": ["2026年02月27日 12時19分39秒"], "項番No.0": [], "項番No.1": ["2026年度", "秋学期／Fall", "火曜３時限／Tuesday 3", "秋学期／Fall", "Ｇ－ＩＳ１０４"]}, "campas": 0, "name": "【320】Foreign Policy Analysis／Foreign Policy Analysis [EN]", "管理部署": 10, "単位数": 2, "担当者": "ウォルシュ　Ｂ．（WALSH BRIAN） ", "履修基準年度": "２年", "履修登録方法": "本登録", "開講期": 2, "時限1": 9, "評価1": 2, "評価2": 5, "成績評価備考": "備考　Note\nStudents will be expected to attend and participate in class discussions and may be asked to complete small assignments from time to time. These will all factor into the participation grade which is 50 percent of the final grade. Finally, there will be a final essay in class worth 50 percent of the grade."}